A Chinese lawmaker has appealed to set up a trans - ministry agency to shoulder the responsibilities, which are undertaken by several government departments, for food safety in the hope of preventing food safety scares.
China's food and drug regulator, kicked off the 2006 food safety evaluation campaign in 31 major cities.
China's quality supervision authorities have blacklisted 14 companies for planning to export substandard food products and banned them from further exports.
